<div data-pcid="1002" class="kedit keditDark" id="kpg_371" data-bgcolor="#F57F17" style="background:#F57F17"><h2 class="keditable"><span style="font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;">AML &amp; CTF Awareness &amp; Prevention</span></h2>
<div class="keditable"><span style="font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;"><i class="*">The ongoing fight against AML/CTF is a challenging area for firms under AML/CTF laws and regulations. Weak AML/CTF controls will open up new vulnerabilities while strong and effective AML/CTF controls will make your firm a difficult target for criminals.</i></span></div></div><div data-pcid="1018" id="kpg_576546" class="kedit">
		
		<div class="keditable"><b>Course Description &amp; Duration</b>&nbsp;<div>This interactive workshop has been designed for managers, supervisors and staff within
the banking and finance industry to raise awareness of the impact of AML/CTF laws and
regulation on their businesses. The course provides delegates with in-depth knowledge,
tools and skills needed to spot ML/TF techniques/indicators.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>This exercise-based workshop employs true-life case studies and videos to highlight the
processes involved in these criminal activities. Delegates are given the opportunity to
devise their own ‘mock’ money laundering schemes and then seek to prevent and
dismantle the schemes devised by their counterparts. This course offers practical skills
and teaches how vigilance and the adoption of appropriate measures can be used to
mitigate ML/TF risks.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>The course is offered as a full day workshop.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div><b>Course Outline&nbsp;</b></div><div><ul><li>The Three stages of Money Laundering.&nbsp;</li><li>Overview of International regulatory bodies and the global framework for combating
ML and CTF.&nbsp;</li><li>Key regulatory requirements for ML/FT detection and prevention.&nbsp;</li><li>Discuss the importance of good KYC/CDD/EDD in ML/CTF risk mitigation.&nbsp;</li><li>Writing a good SAR/STR report.
Group Exercise - Teamwork to devise an effective ML scheme using true life ML/CTF
materials.&nbsp;</li></ul></div><div><br></div><div><b>Training Outcomes</b>&nbsp;</div><div><i>By the end of the training, delegates will be able to:&nbsp;</i></div><div><ul><li>Describe the concept &amp; process of ML and explain the stages involved.&nbsp;</li><li>Explain the ML/CTF laws &amp; regulations, key obligations for regulated firms and the
cost of non-compliance.&nbsp;</li><li>Explain how good KYC/CDD/EDD procedures support financial crime risk prevention.&nbsp;</li><li>Demonstrate an enhance awareness in the knowledge and scope of ML/CT red flags
and indicators.</li></ul></div></div>
			
